The nation was on tenterhooks on Monday after President Jacob Zuma abruptly &ldquo;instructed&rdquo; Finance Minister Pravin Gordhan to return from a scheduled international investor road show.The move by Zuma fuelled speculation of a Cabinet reshuffle and that the long-awaited showdown between him and the minister was imminent.It has long been speculated that Zuma was intent on appointing Brian Molefe as the next political head of the Treasury, a suspicion supported by the former Eskom boss&rsquo; hasty swearing-in as an ANC MP in February. Molefe resigned from power utility Eskom under a cloud last year after being fingered in a &ldquo;state capture&rdquo; interim report by former public protector Thuli Madonsela.If you are already a subscriber, please click on the following link below to go to the full article: Gordhan recall fuels talk of showdownIf you would like to&nbsp;subscribe &nbsp;to BusinessLIVE Premium to read the full story, please&nbsp;click here: SubscribePremium content is not yet available on the app. Please use the desktop site to subscribe.